The collection contains the Original Dancing Baby loop by the orignal creators Michael Girard, Robert Lurye and John Chadwick - plus re-imaginations by Chris Torres, KidEight, Serwah Attafuah, Yuuki Morita, Kreationsministern and YONK.

artworks.name: "The Dancer 2022" by Serwah Attafuah
artworks.description:
The Dancer 2022

„I remixed the Dancing Baby by trying to imagine the baby in one of my digital worlds, and as a part cyborg part human angel. I also took inspiration from Black Sabbath's fallen angel logo.“ - Serwah Attafuah

artworks.name: "Nyan Dancing Baby" by Chris Torres
artworks.description: "During the Internet of 1996, Dancing Baby was born. This legendary meme may very well be the grandfather of all Internet Memes. It was the first meme to break out of the digital world and into mainstream pop culture history leading the way for all other memes to come. I’m honored to be a part of the Dancing Baby celebration and excited to introduce Nyan Dancing Baby."  - Chris Torres, Nyan Cat

artworks.name: The Original Dancing Baby
artworks.description:
The Original Dancing Baby: One of the first viral videos in the history of the internet by the original creator team Michael Girard, Robert Lurye and John Chadwick. They produced a meme before the world actually knew what a meme is.

By owning the digitally restored loop by the original creators, you own part of internet history. 

© 1996 Autodesk, Inc. The Dancing Baby is reproduced and distributed with the permission of Autodesk, Inc. All rights reserved.
